#%RAML 1.0 Library
usage: |
  This library defines reusable security traits for enforcing authentication and authorization
  requirements across APIs.

  As part of the Customer API-led reference architecture, it centralizes common security patterns,
  such as Client ID Enforcement, enabling consistent declaration of required authentication
  mechanisms.

  These traits define the contract between API consumers and the platform, while policy enforcement
  is managed through Anypoint API Manager and the MuleSoft gateway.

  This library is intended for use across System, Process, and Experience APIs to promote consistent
  and reusable security definitions.

traits:
  client-id-enforced:
    displayName: Client ID Enforcement
    description: |
      Specifies that callers must provide valid client application credentials to invoke the
      operation.

      This trait is designed to complement the Client ID Enforcement policy configured in Anypoint
      API Manager. It defines the credential requirements specified in the API specification,
      whereas enforcement occurs at runtime via the API gateway.
    headers:
      client_id:
        displayName: Client ID
        description: Client application identifier.
        type: string
        required: true
        example: 8f3a7b1c2d4e5f6a
      client_secret:
        displayName: Client Secret
        description: Client application secret.
        type: string
        required: true
        example: 4e7c9a1d3f5b8c2e
    responses:
      401:
        description: |
          Authentication failed because the client application credentials were missing, invalid,
          or not authorized for this API.
